	ncipal\, Kreider Hughes Law\, PLLC Patrice is an estate planning and small
	-business attorney with 15\\+ years of experience. She earned her B.A. in 
	psychology from the University of Virginia and her J.D. from Seattle Unive
	rsity School of Law. Before founding Kreider Hughes Law in 2017\, she serv
	ed as in-house counsel for Conover Insurance\, handling mergers and acquis
	itions\, contracts\, and employment matters. Featured on the Seattle Conne
	cted podcast and recognized by Expertise.com in 2023 and 2024\, Patrice li
	ves in Seattle with her wife\, their daughter Simone\, and pets Luther and
	 Emma. Session Outline Why Collaboration Matters Financial planners and es
	tate attorneys working in tandem to build resilient\, values-aligned plans
	. Building Your Planning Team Roles\, responsibilities\, and coordination 
	between advisors who understand LGBTQ\\+ needs. Protecting Assets During Y
	our Lifetime Insurance \\(life\, disability\, long-term care\\)\, investme
	nt strategy \\(diversification\, ESG\\)\, and ownership/titling alignment.
	 Legal Documents That Safeguard Your Wishes Durable POA\, healthcare POA &
	 advance directive\, wills & trusts\, and syncing beneficiary designations
	. Coordinating Asset Transfers Real estate titling\, retirement & insuranc
	e beneficiaries\, business succession\, and philanthropic giving. Navigati
	ng Legal Landscapes & Family Structures Marriage recognition\, parental ri
	ghts\, cross-border/visa considerations\, and state-by-state variability. 
	Q&A \\(15 min\\) - Bring your questions on real estate\, trusts\, chosen f
	amily\, and children's inheritance planning. Who Should Attend LGBTQ\\+ in
	dividuals\, couples\, and families seeking long-term financial security Sm
	all business owners planning for succession and legacy Anyone looking to a
	lign legal and financial strategies\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events
	/#/details/working-together-to-protect-and-transfer-assets-virtual-webinar
	/18089679/2026-03-18T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/working-together-to-prote
	ct-and-transfer-assets-virtual-webinar/18089679/2026-03-18T00
